  "prompt": "What do boxers say to each other when in the ring?",
  "response": "Boxers often engage in various forms of verbal communication during a match, which can include:\n\n1. **Taunts:** Boxers might taunt each other to try to get inside their opponent's head and throw them off their game.\n   \n2. **Encouragement:** Sometimes, boxers will encourage their opponent to hit them, in an effort to show confidence or to goad them into making a mistake.\n\n3. **Strategy:** Some boxers might strategize out loud or call out their next move, either as a psychological tactic or to intimidate their opponent.\n\n4. **Respect:** Occasionally, boxers might show mutual respect and compliment each other on a good shot or round.\n\n5. **General Communication:** Boxers may communicate with their corner or the referee if there\u2019s a concern or to get advice.\n\nHowever, the exact nature of what is said can vary widely depending on the boxers' personalities, styles, and the context of the match.",
